text: Senhit Zadik Zadik (born 1 October 1979), better known by her first name Senhit, is an Eritrean-Italian singer. == Eurovision Song Contest == She represented San Marino in the Eurovision 2011 with the song "Stand By", but did not qualify for the final. Senhit returned to Eurovision in 2021, representing San Marino with her song "Adrenalina". She performed the song with American rapper Flo Rida. They finished 22nd out of 26 entries, with 50 points. == References == Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
